Mission Statement / Editorial Focus:
Able Muse is an independent literary journal (founded in 1999) devoted to publishing masterfully crafted writing and fostering a serious community of readers and writers. We feature poetry—with a special emphasis on metrical and formal verse in a contemporary idiom and exceptional free verse—alongside translation, fiction, creative nonfiction, essays, interviews, reviews, and visual art. Our editorial focus is on work that marries technical skill with imaginative force: language that is precise and memorable, musicality without mannerism, and forms—traditional or innovative—used with purpose and freshness.  Able Muse’s mission extends beyond the journal through a family of related presses and platforms: Able Muse Press (https://www.ablemusepress.com
), Word Galaxy Press (https://www.wordgalaxy.com
), and Many Words Press (https://www.manywords.com
), which publish poetry, fiction, and anthologies by emerging and established writers. We also host Eratosphere (https://www.ablemuse.com/erato
), our long-running online literary workshop and discussion forum dedicated to craft, revision, and literary conversation. Together, these efforts support a culture of attentive reading, rigorous standards, and enduring literary exchange.
